						<summary>

						<p>On a stone pillar lying in a field near the Krishṇā.</p>						

						<p>Siṅghaṇa.</p>						

						<p>After referring to the reign of the king, it praises Bhūtayya Rāhuta, a subordinate of the king.</p>						

						<p>The inscription is damaged and fragmentary.</p>						

						</summary>
